# 💡==============================💡
# most important question why enumerate? 
# enumerate is more pythonic , it better than range(len) as it contain both value and index
#enumerate is like someone handing you both the attendance roll and the student. 
# range(len(...)) is like getting just the roll number and then hunting the student down yourself.
# 💡==============================💡

k = [1,2,3,45,6,7] #for understanding how range works it starts with 0 
for i in range(len(k)):
    print(i)
